The paper deals with the task of automatically generating maps from satellite images using deep learning models. This task involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as image processing and generation, which suggests that cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and RealNVP models, which are popular machine learning (ML) models used in image generation and normalization, respectively. This suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the second most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of loss functions such as reconstruction loss and style transfer loss, which are commonly used in ML models for image processing and generation, indicating that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also deals with the specific task of generating maps, which falls under the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics) and involves the use of computer graphics techniques. Finally, the paper uses deep learning models such as GANs, which are a type of neural network, suggesting that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
